attribute.description:
If allowglissandi is off, each note represents a whole partial (with no possible glissandi), and this attribute determines the way in which pitches and velocities are given to such note:
- First: The partial keeps the pitch and velocity of its first element;
- Mean (default): The partial takes the mean pitch and velocity;
- Median: The partial takes as pitch/velocity the median of the pitches/velocities.
If allowglissandi is on, this attribute does not affect anything.
